    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-19T01:27:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-19T01:27:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <head>137. Telegram From the Commander in Chief, Atlantic (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DARL1" type="from">Dennison</persName>) to the Commander of
                    Special Task Group 81.8 (<persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1" type="to"
                        >Clark</persName>)<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d137fn0">Source: Naval
                        Historical Center, Area Files, Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret; Operational
                        Immediate; Exclusive. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Norfolk</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-04-19T01:27:00-05:00">April 19, 1961, 1:27 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190627Z. Exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName> from
                        <persName corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName>
                    <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1">Gray</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>At your discretion and with due regard for security your forces and need
                        for concealing involvement U.S. conduct eyeball <gloss target="#t_RECCO1"
                            >recco</gloss> objective area first light 19 April.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>New subject. If <gloss target="#t_CEF1">CEF</gloss> effort has not been
                        fully effective desire all <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> earliest as
                        to whether guerilla operations have been started. If this is the case then
                        it might be possible for us to arrange support by air drops etc. As you must
                        realize I am groping in the dark and any <gloss target="#t_info1"
                            >info</gloss> you can supply (possibly through Col Mallardʼs sources)
                        would be of great help.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Another subject. We may be called upon for evacuation of wounded. This
                        might involve helicopters and stop off in Essex prior transfer to yet
                        undetermined destination.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
